latestIgtvVideos.caption:
@abujanisandeepkhosla The night, like our hearts, is a young and wild thing. 

‘Into the Light - a film by Abu Jani Sandeep Khosla and Joseph Radhik that celebrates couture like never before. 

‘Into the Light’ has finally conjured a long brewing fantasy. For the past year, Abu Sandeep have been captivated by the possibility of creating a film that goes far beyond fashion. Much before ‘Into the Light’ manifested as reality, Sandeep had written to Joseph about the idea, knowing well in his heart that only they can bring this hypnotizing dream to fruition.

A very Special Thank You to @norafatehi

latestPosts.caption:
@jacquelienefernandez one of the honourees @redseafilm for the “Women in Cinema” Gala at @hotelducapedenroc ♥️🌹♥️

Our 2nd consecutive @festivaldecannes together ♥️
(And my 5th year at the festival.)

We both knew we wanted to do red and elegance, and I’m currently obsessed with all things roses. 

People’s judgements may last only a few seconds, but behind every look is weeks of preparation, sourcing gowns straight from world wide ateliers, coordinating with designers and jewellers, managing customs delays, tailoring garments/fittings to perfection under impossible time constraints.

Cannes always reminds me why I love this work. It’s demanding, yes — but it’s also deeply rewarding. To be part of fashion history, to see your vision come to life on one of the world’s most iconic stages in the French Riviera, that’s the kind of magic I’ll never get tired of.

Thank you to each one of my collaborators for making this vision a reality ♥️🌹

Styling @mayemusk in Mumbai one day after her birthday (the flowers in the background were sent by Elon!), in @anamikakhanna.in , and placing her first ever “bindi” on her forehead, was not on my 2025 bingo card 💫

What an absolute pleasure to dress a woman I have long admired, for her book release in Hindi in India. 
“A Woman Makes A Plan”

Maye loves colour and to be comfortable, so this Anamika Khanna was her undisputed first choice. She quietly admired the hand embroidery and craftsmanship. Being a model for over 50 years, she truly is beautiful inside and out.
